<Content>Perfect place to stay in Florence We spent 4 nights at Residence Hilda in Florence in January, a good time to visit. Not only is Residence Hilda a beautifully renovated appartment hotel with designer flair, it is also in the perfect location. It is only a short walking distance to the Duomo, other tourist attractions and the main shopping area, so that you can walk everywhere.The hotel itself is extremely clean, the kitchen is well-equipped and it is a wonderful place to relax after a hard day's sightseeing and shopping. Better than sitting on the edge of a bed in a cramped hotel room ! Our appartment had a large bedroom with its own TV, a sitting area with another TV, sofa bed, armchairs and a separate kitchen/diner. They had obviously given a lot of thought to what travellers want - there were lots of lovely touches, such as providing candles for a romantic evening. The staff were very helpful and friendly and the service is excellent. We had forgotten to pack a jacket and Valentina wrote us an e-mail offering to send it to us free of charge. That's what I call service. We were very impressed.Tania 
