<Author>Vagabond20
<Content>Excellent for families I have been to Florence seven times in ten years and this is the best place I have stayed (although not the most expensive). The staff are all lovely, the location is excellent and the apartments are spacious, modern, beautifully furnished and well equipped. There is a very decent little Conad supermarket 100 yards along Via dei Servi (on the left as you walk towards the Duomo) and the staff will get groceries for you before your arrival if you e-mail them a grocery list. There is also a nice cafe on the street right next door, a laundromat across the street and I can even recommend the interestingly named Isabel Vegas hair salon across the street for a stylish blow dry.You can walk to the Duomo in about three minutes and to the Piazza di Signora in less than ten. The Mercato Centrale is also less than ten minutes walk away. The food market there is well worth a visit to enjoy your self catering digs to maximum advantage!Our 2nd floor apartment had a good master bedroom and twin beds set up in the sitting room and the roomy hallway. My kids (ages 10 and 12) were comfortable and enjoyed fairly good privacy. The twin beds were much better than your average rollaway.I highly recommend Residence Hilda and I think Valentina at the front desk is particularly to be commended for her cheerfulness, excellent English and enthusiasm to see that her guests are well looked after. I look forward to returning! 
