<Content>RH is the Place It's tough to find quad accomodations in an old city. We found the ideal place in Florence. Residence Hilda is in a wonderful location, literally one block from the Accademia, 2 from the Duomo, and just minutes from all the other major Florence sites. RH is not a hotel, more like a boutique apartment building. Our suite had a large master bedroom, two twin beds in the hallway, and eat-in kitchen. The kitchen is good enough for simple meal preparation. They even provide salt, pepper, vinegar and olive oil. The only bad things I can say about the accomodations is that the ventilation in the bathroom was weak, and the shower has this cool looking and utterly stupid semi-partition instead of a proper curtain or door so water gets everywhere. I paid around $400/night, which is a good value considering the quality and location. Our receptionist, Valentina, was very sweet, and gave us good advice. We were there for Easter weekend, and we were pleasantly surprised to find traditional Tuscan treats waiting for us when we returned from a day of sightseeing. The hotel is close enough to the central bus/train station to walk (10-15 minutes), but I would recommend a taxi if you've got sizeable luggage or small kids. 
