<Content>Great place to stay! We spent three nights at Residence Hilda with our 11 year old daughter in May, and we wished we could have stayed longer. The location was fabulous: a stroll to the Duomo, yet away from the noise and the hawkers. The staff were very helpful and thoughtful, and provided some great restaurant suggestions. Their extremely detailed directions sent to us by email were a lifesaver, as we were arriving by car. Our suite was spacious and very tastefully furnished in contemporary style, with a nice large bathroom, a seperate bedroom, and a lounge/dining/kitchen area which was light and very comfortable. It was cleaned daily, including any dishes that were left out. There is a well stocked supermarket in the street which is handy for snacks if you are travelling with children, and the pastry shop downstairs is wonderful. There is a very clean laundromat opposite, again very useful for families. As we were there on the weekend, the only slight inconvenience was a little bit of street noise at night from people walking around (no traffic noise, as it is a pedestrian zone). That would be the case anywhere in central Florence, and could be dealt with by shutting windows and turning on the aircon instead. We chose not to do that ( prefering the fresh air and downtown atmosphere!) and were rewarded by the sound of early morning rain on the clay rooftops, followed by Sunday morning bellringing: magic! All in all, a very friendly, stylish and comfortable place to stay, we can't wait to go back! 
